<specimenCount id="9D5CAFDAD966FF914340E87AFC76FDF4" box="[862,897,547,573]" pageId="1" pageNumber="427" type="male">1♂</specimenCount>
larvae were collected and successfully raised to emergence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE56453D966FF9140D9E833FCFCFD04" blockId="1.[151,1437,474,717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis id="B92EB841D966FF9140D9E833FED8FD4D" bold="true" box="[199,303,618,644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="427">Habitus:</emphasis>
Body small (body length including caudal lamellae 
<quantity id="4CA2C9B6D966FF914399E833FC0FFD4C" box="[903,1016,618,645]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="427" unit="mm" value="16.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="15.0">15–18mm</quantity>
long), smooth and moderately stout, lacking distinct bands or marks, with broad paddle-shaped caudal lamellae (
<figureCitation id="136178D6D966FF9143FBE8D6FBDCFD60" box="[997,1067,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1985,2009]" captionTargetBox="[406,1180,751,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-150@1.[393,1195,741,1962]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Final instar larva H. latiloba habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6544307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6544307/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="427">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136178D6D966FF914427E8D6FBA1FD60" box="[1081,1110,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[181,1410,181,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[178,1410,181,1883]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 7. Larvae and adults of two Huosoma species: (a) male larva of H. latiloba; (b) emerging adult male of H. latiloba; (c) mating pair of H. latiloba, Mt. Cangshan, Dali City, Yunnan Province (photo by Guo-Hui Yang); (d) larva of H. tinctipenne ready to feed on the larvae of Chironomidae; (e) final stadium larva of H. tinctipenne; (f) adult female of H. tinctipenne, Yunlong County, Dali City, Yunnan Province (photo by Guo-Hui Yang)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538341/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="427">7a</figureCitation>
). Males and females are very similar except for presence of an ovipositor in the latter.
</paragraph>
